        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : \"Then spake one after this manner, and the other spake after another manner.\" In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 18:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the indefinite אי־זה of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 22:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is elucidated by הדּרך זה אי, \"is that the manner\" (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 13:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 3:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")., and the verb. עבר follows without the relative pronoun, as in the passages cited. In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 18:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", only הרכב שׂרי of the king are mentioned, without any statement of the number, which is given in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 22:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with a backward reference to the former war (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 20:24",
